cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.SY, cs.MM, cs.DC

Reasoning: 
1. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper focuses on resource allocation in a two-tier HetNet, which involves network architecture and communication protocols. 
2. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper proposes a transmission protocol and performs time resource allocation to maximize network capacity, which involves information theory concepts. 
3. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper proposes a two-step strategy to tackle the resource allocation problem, which involves system modeling and control. 
4. cs.MM (Multimedia) - The paper considers mixed traffic consisting of best effort traffic and soft QoS traffic, which involves multimedia applications. 
5. cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) - The paper proposes an efficient iterative algorithm to solve the resource allocation problem, which involves distributed computing concepts.
